laces the problem of corporate irresponsibility within the broader context of American life and demonstrates the extent to which contemporary corporate behavior represents a corruption of our cherished liberal values of personal freedom and individuality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCorporationsxCorrupt practicesxUnited States. 0aCorporationsxCorrupt practiceszUnited States. 0aCorporationsxMoral and ethical aspectsxUnited States. 0aCorporationsxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aEntreprisesxPratiques déloyalesxÉtats-Unis. 0aEntreprisesxResponsabilité socialexÉtats-Unis. 0aMorale des affairesxÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 0aSocial responsibility of businessxUnited States. 0aSocial responsibility of businesszUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013776740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300137767423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300137767/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles